London m. Henry Sollier
mj last to you was on the p sritt sence reed yd of 3 & 7d as to the bill
of LK. you have seen my letter to hum, then by you forund that I am sadclud
to bu, & beeng vere much sracqned straighned on all sides, do not know ow
to rimbouise m, except you please to repay un £100- for my acctt & the
I'll replace the £100- you desire, for upon what prssext can s keep dun
from du mony, which I bught to have remitted di longe sence, & I
paij the bill, & redrad att on you att 2zo, what shall re iudge thenofince
whece as je exspected the valew longe sence, so I kow nothing beeter then thet
you please to pay sus £100- for my acctt. I have examined yd. standcy out
debts of last ye, a finde yett above £500 slemish, so that I can not do whit
I will, there by itt is now our principall time to buy witer provisions, so that
never in this wald I was so much pincled as now in am. as to the £35-
I feund itt is my oune mistake, so have given you onely creditt for the
£7„14. 8 80 pay to m. Pindar, the rest beeng to my owne, as to the
resting cloathes, our sale comen ene after harvest, & then I'll do my endeavour
as for mr. Warner, I hope de is well arrived, I shanck you, that you word
be pleased to speake to him in my behalf, I iiudge itt needless, for snew
mett yett an englessman, which I less knew then hm, & because I supese
though itt may be Iam mistaken that de is vere presmtious, so will let
dun follon dis owne Bunmour, when you was here you proomised my tospeds
to the excentone of m. w de reysters estate, about dis signing the compositin
of dansel vivan without ord. of daniel disschop for £80- pray if you can
do any good uyon that, itt will be rewarded so content inclised is the
allestaions
C 22d.
Dublin Elnatam Lumm
In answerto yot of 27th past, laces &ie fallen by 10 p & ace now pare good, &
white, because the frerch have lately imposed great duties on them, so that thad
is not so muel exported that way as sere before where fore I shall be able
to compleat yds parell in a short wbile, whilst I do wite this day to ostend
to know if oy oprtunte be then of shipping, if not, shall be sent tobRottnden
as formeely, I shall rembourse my self on m. Cole, & advise you the needfull

London George Cole
mij last toyou was on the 18 suitt. to which referre you, sence save recd order fomm lun
of du blin to draw on you for ii acctt. abour £150- so please to advise mee if you
shall do mee good such valen, ot there abouts, which then shall be past to the
fallance of JD: deseated, & for what I desired m. Casta brook of Epon to draw
on you. besides this I boubt I must seuble you for some thing more to acopty
mr. lobbers, which you might redraw on mee though the nette jumm I know
not yett, butt shall advise you, whilst in exspecitation of yd answere
